article.description: Jamelle Cornley had 22 points and six rebounds, leading sixth-seeded Penn State past Indiana for a 66-51 victory in the first round of the Big Ten tournament.

images.caption: Matt Roth and Brett Finkelmeier sum up a dismal season at Indiana.

related.description: The record was Indiana's worst in 93 years. But the '08-09 Hoosiers deserve a hearty handshake for sticking it out.
related.title: Gene Wojciechowski: Indiana's season over the brink
related.headline: Record suffered; pride didn't at Indiana

article.headline: Penn State to face Purdue in second round
article.linkText: Cornley's 22 power Penn State past Indiana
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS -- Jamelle Cornley had 22 points and six rebounds, leading sixth-seeded Penn State past Indiana for a 66-51 victory in the first round of the Big Ten tournament. The sixth-seeded Nittany Lions (22-10) won for the fourth time in six games and advanced to Friday's semifinals against third-seeded Purdue. Another win would put Penn State in Saturday's semifinals and likely lock up their first NCAA tournament bid since 2001. Indiana (6-25) was led by Verdell Jones with 23 points. But the Hoosiers lost their 10th straight and finished with the school's lowest win total since 1915-16.
